{"question": "What does Affordability option C mean?", "answer": "Affordability option C means that within any eligible site, excluding the geographic area south of ninety-sixth street in the borough of Manhattan and other excluded areas in the city of New York, at least thirty percent of the dwelling units are affordable housing one hundred thirty percent units. Additionally, the eligible site must be developed without substantial assistance from grants, loans, or subsidies provided by a federal, state, or local governmental agency or instrumentality for affordable housing development."}
